  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1726",
  "title": "Add search for facet capabilities in InstantSearch.js",
  "body": "**This is for instantsearch.js**\r\n\r\n## Use case\r\n\r\nThere is no search for facet values. It means that a user using a refinement list does not have the ability to search into the values. We conduct a small UX study and this is the next step, the actual implementation.\r\n\r\n![screenshot 2016-12-09 14 56 28](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/393765/21051252/b1181614-be1f-11e6-90ae-5c9e636deeff.png)\r\n\r\n## Proposed API\r\n\r\nUse the current refinementList widget and add two new options:\r\n - *searchForValues*: boolean - true if we want the end user to be able to search for facet values\r\n - *searchPlaceholder*: string - the placeholder used",
